[[{{PAGENAME}}]] is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Japan]]. It is the main shrine of Iizuka in Fukuoka.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ojisanjake |title=Noso Hachimangu |url=https://www.ojisanjake.com/2016/02/noso-hachimangu.html |access-date=2023-10-20 |language=en}}</ref>

It is a [[Beppyo shrine]], or a shrine that is particularly notable in a certain way with a significant history to it.<ref>{{Cite web |title=別表神社とは？御朱印めぐりに参考になる「別表神社一覧」とマップ {{!}} 開運戦隊ゴシュインジャー |url=https://jinja-gosyuin.com/beppyou/ |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=jinja-gosyuin.com}}</ref>

It is a [[Hachiman shrine]], or a shrine dedicated to the [[kami]] [[Hachiman]]<ref name="bunpu">{{cite web |last=Motegi |first=Sadazumi |title=Shamei Bunpu (Shrine names and Distributions) |url=http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=776 |accessdate=23 March 2010 |publisher=Encyclopedia of Shinto |language=Japanese}}</ref><!--I think this is sufficient citation but it is just about interpreting the name-->

